) an altered form of this, reflecting the Canadian and American French practice of sounding the final <i>-t</i>."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William Malet was born in 1125, in Curry Mallet, Somerset, England, his father, Robert De Malet, was 37 and his mother, Hesilia Crispin, was 45. He married Hesilla Crispen Brionne in 1145, in Somerset, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1169, in his hometown, at the age of 44."},"et":{"1125–1169":"1125–1169","1127–1197":"1127–1197","1120–Female":"1120–Surnud","1129–1213":"1129–1213","1150–1194":"1150–1194","1125–Male":"1125–Surnud","1169–1199":"1169–1199","1088–1155":"1088–1155","1080–1125":"1080–1125","1080":"1080","1088":"1088","1120":"1120","1197":"1197","1194":"1194","1150":"1150","Bef 1120":"enne 1120","1129":"1129","1127":"1127","Abt 1150":"umbes 1150","1125":"1125","1169":"1169","1213":"1213","1145":"1145","1155":"1155","1199":"1199","Somerset, England":"Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Curry Mallet, Somerset, England":"Curry Mallet, Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Curry Mallet, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Curry Mallet, Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1125–1169":"1125–1169